> **Agent-facing tool rule:** The user normally does not need to edit this file.

This project is a Workspace OS workspace.

- Read @AGENTS.md and @INDEX.md before working.
- Follow @agents/workspace-chief.md as the coordinator.
- On session start, run the lightweight structural reconciliation in @AGENTS.md so manually added
  folders, subfolders, and files are indexed and integrated automatically.
- Ground relevant work in @{{DOCS_ROOT}}/workspace-profile.md.
- Treat `{{DOCS_ROOT}}/` as the user's primary working surface. Respect the focused areas kept during
  personalization; do not recreate removed starter folders without a current need.
- Apply @_workspace_setup_docs/skills/apply-workspace-struct.md after meaningful changes.
- Determine from meaning and scope whether guidance is task-local or a durable operating preference;
  do not rely on trigger phrases. When one request contains both immediate work and a reusable
  convention, complete both the artifact and the best-practice update.
- Preserve raw input, create clean artifacts separately, and update the nearest indexes.
- Route repeatable preferences to @agents/sub-agents/skill-librarian.md and keep
  `workspace-best-practices/skills/`, templates, specialists, routes, and links synchronized.
- Treat `workspace-best-practices/` as the shared customization center: skills control workflows and
  outputs, templates control exact formats, and references teach examples, voice, and style.
- Never leave stale links, orphaned routes, or undocumented artifacts after adds, moves, renames, or
  removals.
